火影忍者電子遊戲已在[[任天堂|任天堂]]、[[索尼|索尼]]和[[微軟|微軟]]等各家遊戲平台上發行。大多為[[格鬥遊戲|格鬥遊戲]]，由玩家控制一名火影忍者角色。玩家將與{{tsl|en|Artificial intelligence in video games|遊戲AI}}或[[多人電子遊戲|其他玩家控制的角色]]進行對抗；目標是藉由基本攻擊及源自角色在火影忍者原作裡的特殊技能將對手擊倒。<ref name="GameSpotHandsOnCoN1">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/naruto-clash-of-ninja-updated-hands-on/1100-6144888/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170315122904/http://www.gamespot.com/articles/naruto-clash-of-ninja-updated-hands-on/1100-6144888/ |archive-date=2017-03-15 |title=Naruto: Clash of Ninja Updated Hands-On |website=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]] |last=Torres |first=Ricardo |date=2006-02-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>第一款火影忍者電子遊戲為《火影忍者：木葉忍法帖》，於2003年3月27日在日本發行，使用[[WonderSwan|WonderSwan Color]]作為遊戲平台。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/naruto-konoha-ninpouchou/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303135226/http://www.gamespot.com/naruto-konoha-ninpouchou/ |archive-date=2017-03-03 |title=GameSpot: Naruto: Konoha Ninpouchou |website=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]]|url-status=dead }}</ref>大多數火影忍者電子遊戲僅在日本發行。首先發行海外的遊戲是《{{tsl|en|Naruto: Clash of Ninja (series)|火影忍者：激鬥忍者大戰！}}》系列和《{{tsl|en|Naruto: Ninja Council (series)|火影忍者：忍術全開！最強忍者大結集}}》系列。<ref name="ClashofNinjaAnnouncement">{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/gamecube/action/naruto/news.html?sid=6141993&mode=all |title=Shonen Jump's Naruto Coming to North America! |website=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628212936/http://www.gamespot.com/gamecube/action/naruto/news.html?sid=6141993&mode=all |archive-date=2011-06-28 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="NinjaCouncilGeneralInfo">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/games/naruto-ninja-council/gba-497565 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160413132707/http://www.ign.com/games/naruto-ninja-council/gba-497565 |archive-date=2016-04-13 |title=IGN: Naruto: Ninja Council |website=[[IGN|IGN]]|url-status=dead }}</ref>2012年1月，[[萬代南夢宮娛樂|萬代南夢宮]]宣布他們已在全球售出1000萬部火影忍者遊戲。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-01-12/10-million-naruto-games-shipped |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114071503/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-01-12/10-million-naruto-games-shipped |archive-date=2016-11-14 |title=10 Million Naruto Games Shipped |work=[[Anime_News_Network|Anime News Network]]|date=2012-01-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

